    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/991.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>An imposing demonstration favoring the commission will be held this afternoon.
                    Negotiations up to date have created a strong pro-American sentiment among the
                    people and the country is for the first time enjoying a considerable measure of
                    freedom of speech and of the press. All this is believed to be due to a better
                    understanding of President Wilson’s attitude, explained in the Mobile speech,
                    which we had published here in full.</p>
                <p>The Dominican Government’s attempt to create hostility to the commission is
                    therefore meeting with failure. A demonstration for this purpose was to have
                    occurred yesterday but has been postponed until the Government can obtain
                    mercenary attendants. The Government is misrepresenting our attitude by using
                    the words “supervision,” “intervention,” “control.”</p>
                <p>In view of the misrepresentation by the Government, may I publish the open
                    telegrams from the Department?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
